'''''The Muncher''''' is a video game for the [[Commodore 64]] and [[ZX Spectrum]] that was released in 1988.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://spectrumcomputing.co.uk/index.php?cat=96&id=3323|title=The Muncher|work=SpectrumComputing.co.uk}}</ref> It was produced by [[Krome Studios Melbourne|Beam Software]] and released by [[Gremlin Interactive|Gremlin Graphics]]. The game involves the monster from ''[[Chewits]]'' attacking modern day Japan.<ref>{{cite magazine|magazine=[[Sinclair User]]|title=Full Page Advert|page=97|date=March 1989|issue=84|url=https://archive.org/details/sinclair-user-magazine-084/page/n97/mode/2up}}</ref>

==Gameplay==
The objective is to cause as much destruction as possible in a 2D setting town. Points are awarded for various buildings destroyed. The monster has fire breath and can destroy buildings in this way.

